          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1458.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the cauliflower is cooking, peel and finely slice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>onion</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
