    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse the<strong> red lentils </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>rinsed</strong> <strong>lentils</strong>, <strong>chopped spinach</strong> and <strong>tamarind stock</strong>, then reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 25-30 min or until the lentils are cooked and the sauce has thickened – this is your <strong>spinach & tamarind dal</strong></p>",
